<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 6:25PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Davidson, northwestern Montgomery, southwestern Randolph and
northeastern Stanly Counties through 700 PM EDT...
At 625 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
High Rock Lake, or 12 miles northwest of Badin Lake, moving east at
15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Badin Lake, Denton, Richfield, New London, Eldorado, Fish Tales
Marina, Finger, High Rock Lake, Whip-O-Will Campground and Newsom.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
